<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1275" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1275">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5424.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Commodore</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 20, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I am advised by your note of yesterday that the Federal Government has
                            ordered the closing of the port of Vera Cruz. I take the liberty to make
                            it known that this is the first notice of the fact which I have
                            received.</p>
                        <p>I also note the action which you took, without the knowledge of this
                            Consulate, in reference to the entrance of the merchant steamer <hi rend="italic">Seguranza.</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>I have ordered a copy of the before-mentioned communication sent to the
                            Department of State of the Government of the United States, to the
                            Ambassador of the same country in Mexico, and to the captain of the <hi rend="italic">Seguranza</hi>.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. W. Canada.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>